g weather (critical), excellent computer skills (tech). Weaknesses: weak memory for numbers (could affect calculations), nasty remarks/uncooperative (teamwork issue), grumpy. So technical good but teamwork poor.\n\nC: Quick correct decisions (good), keeps calm in crisis (good), understands complicated technology (technical), but difficulty communicating ideas (teamwork), egocentric, not willing to further education (development). So technical and decision-making good, but communication and development weak.\n\nD: Responds to unexpected events adequately (good), concentrates well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously (reliability). Weaknesses: know-it-all (could affect crew), hot temper (stress). Technical competence not explicitly mentioned but problem solving suggests competence. No explicit mention of weather, navigation, etc.\n\nWe need to pick best overall. Likely A or C? A has strong leadership but interpersonal issues (show-off, not open). C has communication difficulty and egocentric, also not willing to further education. B has teamwork issues. D has temper issues.\n\nThus A seems strongest overall despite show-off and closedness. But we need to consider that not open to new ideas could be serious for long-distance where tech updates. Show-off may affect crew but leadership may offset. D's hot temper could be dangerous under long flights. B's uncooperative is also serious. C's egocentric and communication issues also serious.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate A.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: need more info on D's technical competence, B's memory impact, C's willingness to improve, A's openness to new ideas. Ask others for D's technical skills, C's teamwork strengths, B's memory mitigation.\n\nNow produce public message."}
